Nested classes in java

[Nested classes in java](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/nested-classes-in-java/)

A class inside another class is known as nested class (inner class). A nested class can be private.

Syntax:

class A // outer class
{
   ......
   class B // nested class
   {
      .....
   }
}

Nested classes in java are divided into two, they are â€“

static nested classes.
non-static nested classes (inner classes).
